{
  "texts": [
    "Another popular metric is the confusion matrix (see Fig. 14b), which displays the ability of an ANN to associate each input pattern with its corresponding class (in this example a digit from 0 to 9) and allows to graphically represent the inference accuracy for each possible input.",
    "Also, the loss function used for training is a critical metric.",
    "One of the most commonly employed loss functions is the Cross-Entropy (see Fig. 14c and Table 2), which can be computed as the difference between the predicted value by the ANN and the true value.",
    "Last but not least, other relevant metrics include the Sensitivity (Fig. 14d), Specificity (Fig.",
    "14e), Precision (Fig. 14f), F-1 score (Fig."
  ]
}